    "text": "Inhibiting the expression of the FtIST1 gene in Tartary buckwheat by VIGS decreased the activities of antioxidant enzymes SOD, POD, and CAT. It increased plasmalemma permeability and leaf Na+ content. This indicates that loss of FtIST1 gene expression leads to decreased antioxidant capacity, increased cell membrane damage, increased shoot Na+ content, and decreased salt tolerance. FtIST1 is a salt tolerance gene associated with salt tolerance in Tartary buckwheat.",
